TCP uses flags to manage the state of every connection.

SYN – Initiates a connection.
ACK – Acknowledges received data.
PSH – Immediately deliver buffered data to the application.
RST – Abruptly terminate a connection.
FIN – Gracefully close a connection.
URG – Indicates urgent data.
Cybersecurity Relevance

Abnormal TCP flag combinations often indicate malicious activity, scanning, or denial-of-service attacks.

SYN packets are commonly abused during SYN Flood attacks.

RST packets can terminate legitimate sessions.

