Blue Team (Defenders)

Process: Detect abnormal flag patterns, identify SYN floods, and configure SYN cookies or firewall protections.

End Goal: Prevent connection exhaustion and detect suspicious TCP behavior.

Red Team (Attackers)

Process: Use SYN scans to enumerate services without completing connections, inject RST packets to disrupt communications, or launch SYN Flood attacks.

End Goal: Gather reconnaissance or deny service to target systems.
